  "adaptive_fix_note": "v1 adaptive refinement started from 100 points (below the starvation cliff at N=1000), causing the base model to be completely wrong before any refinement. Adaptive point selection used a failed model \u2014 every region showed high residual, making selection effectively random. Result: adaptive L2 ROSE from 2.5 to 3.4 over 10 rounds. v2 starts from 500 points (above cliff), pre-trains for 5000 epochs to reasonable convergence, then applies adaptive refinement. LR is reset to 0.0005 at the start of each round.",
